<P>
   ELIZABETH _ Movie review: ``Elizabeth,'' with Cate
Blanchett.``This opulent period film puts a slight feminist gloss
on the early reign of 16th-century monarch, Elizabeth I, showing
her transformation from a radiant, saucy innocent to a polished,
guarded ruler (sort of the total woman, Elizabethan-style). ''
Grade: A- (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-RUGRATS _ Movie review: ``The Rugrats Movie.'' Movie
based on Nickelodeon TV hit. ```The Rugrats Movie' takes the
Nickelodeon hit from the small screen to the big. And it tackles a
big subject matter: making room for baby. Adults will probably feel
antsier than the children, having to listen to adult actors
performing in baby voices, and mispronouncing words in
gosh-darn-cute-kid fashion. But hey, look at it this way: It could
be another Barney flick, or a Teletubbies feature.'' (StMurray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-CELEBRITY _ Movie review: ``Celebrity.'' ``...perhaps
(Woody) Allen himself has been famous for too long. His film is
less a thought-through investigation of an omnipresent phenomenon
than a scattershot series of sketches about supermodels,
hotel-trashing movie stars (Leonardo DiCaprio), the art world, etc.
(Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). Grade: C.
</P>
