</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ For a while I thought Clinton's
reckless sexual acts and lying would open the way to a right-wing
takeover of government. Instead the Republicans lost the last
election big-time, and Newt Gingrich was the one who had to leave
office in shame. How can you hate a scenario like that? One or two
more reports on Clinton's sex life, and San Francisco will be the
new capital of the United States. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   SALTER-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ Who says technology is king? In
the stinging cold sea waters that surround Norway, millions of
codfish have rendered some highly sophisticated sonar tracking
equipment essentially impotent. By STEPHANIE SALTER.
</P>
