   GETTYSBURG-ADDRESS (Danville, Calif.) _ Nov. 19 is the 135th
anniversary of the Gettysburg Address. On that day in 1863, with
the Civil War only half over and the worst yet to come, Abraham
Lincoln delivered a speech now universally regarded as both the
most important oration in U.S. history and the best explanation _
``government of the people, by the people, for the people'' _ of
why this nation exists. By CYNTHIA BASS.
</P>
