</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS (Boston) _ Hal Gill is back in business on the
blueline, again paired with Ray Bourque. By Allen Lessels.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-RYAN-COLUMN (Boston) -- What kind of a political system do
we have if one locally elected official is allowed to become the
unofficial state dictator? By Bob Ryan.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SKIING (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SKI-CANNON (Franconia, N.H.) -- Despite being well back in fast
detachable lifts, snowmaking and grooming, on-slope restaurants and
condos, Cannon Mountain is still a standard. By Tony Chamberlain.
</P>
<P>
   SKI-COLUMN (Undated) _ As planet ski rotates into the season of
'98-99 we consider some of the trends, megatrends, minitrends, and
negatrends. By Tony Chamberlain.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
