<P>
   APPLES-MILWAUKEE (Milwaukee) _ Sometimes, from some angles,
Milwaukee can fool you. Is this Chicago? There's the lake: the same
immense lake, Lake Michigan, stretching to the horizon. Both cities
have bold, modern trademark buildings with prominent zigzag braces.
Both cities nurture old-country traditions, exuberantly celebrated
at annual festivals. Both have mastered the Midwestern knack of
keeping their feet on the ground. But Milwaukee, as its visitors
bureau proclaimed in an advertising campaign a few years back, is
Chicago several million people ago. By R.W. Apple Jr. (Story will
move with a ``t'' category code)
</P>
