<P>
   IMPEACH-CLIFFORD (Washington) _ On a day when the long knives
were showing in Washington's most partisan and unseemly drama, a
separate event _ a memorial service for Clark Clifford _ harked to
a different and more genteel era in the capital, when a small
number of wise men ran the show, and did so discreetly. By R.W.
Apple Jr.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-WILLEY (Washington) _ The four people subpoenaed by the
Judiciary committee Wednesday to testify all have to do with the
Kathleen Willey aspect of Starr's case, and point to the
committee's interest in whether the administration or its allies
attempted to intimidate a witness. By Neil A. Lewis. (600 words)
