<P>
   JUNK-F00D-TRAVEL-TEX (Undated) _ Most of us are more garbage pit
than gourmet. When was the last time you sat down to a meal with
more than two or three courses? Now think back to your most recent
bite of vending-machine cuisine. Bet that was easier. Don't be
embarrassed. The folks at the Snack Food Association of America
estimate that each American eats 21.6 pounds of savory snacks a
year. That's stuff like potato chips, pretzels and beef jerky. We
eat even more of the sweet stuff: an average of 23.5 pounds per
person, and half of that is chocolate. So on your next vacation,
try foodie tourism with more mass appeal: Take a junk-food junket.
By Sarah Yoest.
