   IMPEACH-MEMBERS (Washington) _ The House Judiciary Committee,
known as the most fiercely polarized panel on Capitol Hill, did not
disappoint Thursday. During a full day of testimony, Democrats and
Republicans sparred repeatedly as they tried to either savage or
laud independent counsel Kenneth Starr. By Eric Schmitt and Lizette
Alvarez.
