   CALIFORNIA -- POOR. San Francisco will receive roughly $7
million toward low-income housing, the government announced
Thursday. The $152 million in federal dollars will be used to build
100 units of housing to be used by poor seniors and the disabled.
The location of the apartments will be announced this afternoon.
Stricherz
