months ago when he came in to begin his shift at WCI Steel in
Warren and found he had been laid off. But James Frazier, another
of roughly 200 steel workers laid off at WCI, said he had heard
rumors that something like this was coming. Both men blame the
dumping of cheap foreign steel on the domestic market for
endangering their jobs. (Working -- project.) Gorman
</P>
