   SOCIAL-SECURITY _ WASHINGTON _ House Republicans said Thursday
they expected President Clinton to come forward with the first
proposals to rescue Social Security's finances _ signaling that
they wanted the president to walk point in the jungle warfare that
will be the process of reforming the retirement system. (Lipman,
Cox News Service).
</P>
