<P>
   BBN-MVP _ Sammy Sosa won the National League Most Valuable
Player in a landslide over Mark McGwire, his rival in the most
memorable home run chase ever. Sosa, who finished second to McGwire
with 66 homers, got 30 of 32 first-place votes and 438 points in
balloting by the Baseball Writers' Association of America.
(Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   NFL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-NOTES _ Falcons notebook. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 38.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BEARS _ The Chicago Bears, who play the Atlanta Falcons
Sunday, have gone from the emotional highs of the 1980s into a funk
in the 1990s. And things continue to look bleak. (Bunn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15-18.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DOLPHINS _ Monday night's Dolphins opponent, the New England
Patriots, have gone from a Super Bowl team to one that will need a
miracle just to make the playoffs this year. They've suffered a
slew of injuries; coach Pete Carroll finds himself under fire. What
went wrong? (D'Angelo, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BENGALS _ CINCINNATI _ This is the third year the Bengals
have either changed coaches or quarterbacks in mid-season. They
were dramatically better the last two time, for that season at
least. (Ludwig, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFLBEST _ Highlights from upcoming NFL weekend.
(Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13-15.
</P>
