   FBC-FSU-FLA-PLAYS _ Story, with diagram, on the
``bread-and-butter'' plays of UF and FSU. (Clarke/Dolch, Palm Beach
Post)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-AGGIES _ Can the Aggies hold Ricky Williams under 63 yards
and deny him the NCAA all-time rushing record when the two teams
meet Nov. 27? The Aggies don't think so. (Riggs, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   FBC-COACHES _ It's only fitting that Clemson and South Carolina
meet Saturday in the season finale for both teams. Clemson has
struggled with a 2-8 record while South Carolina is even worse at
1-9. Head coach Tommy West of Clemson was fired Thursday and Brad
Scott of South Carolina is rumored to be in jeopardy of losing his
job. The outcome of Saturday's game could go a long way in
determining Scott's fate. (Wilkinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UGA-OLMISS _ Romaro Miller and Deuce McAllister are not
household names, but the Georgia defensive players are well aware
of the two players. They are the top offensive threats for
Mississippi, and the Bulldogs must stop those two to have any
success in Saturday's SEC game in Athens. (PBrice, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATECH-WAKE _ Georgia Tech's improved pass rush during the
last three games can be attributed to the play of Jesse Tarplin,
who has become the leader of the Jackets' defensive front. Tarplin
and the Jackets figure to face a stiff challenge this weekend
against Wake Forest and its pass-happy attack led by quarterback
Brian Kuklick. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-FSU-QBACK _ Injuries to Dan Kendra and Chris Weinke have
thrust Marcus Outzen into the starting quarterback's job at Florida
State. Now the redshirt sophomore has the most important job on a
team that's contending for a national championship. Outzen has been
steady in his performances this season, but will face his toughest
challenge against a Florida defense that ranks among the nation's
best. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
