<P>
   BIZ-MEGASHIPS (Undated) _ Megaships are taking over the world's
ocean freight traffic, but they don't yet have a port in the United
States that can handle them. One port on each coast will get the
billions of dollars in investment needed to accommodate these
thousand-foot-long behemoths and the huge flow of freight traffic
and jobs they will bring. On the west coast, Los Angeles-Long Beach
is already building the necessary facilities, but which port will
be chosen in the East? Five ports are competing _ New York,
Baltimore, Norfolk, Quonset, R.I. and Halifax, Nova Scotia _ but
three of the five will be cut from the list in the next week or two
by Maersk-Sealand, the huge shipping consortium that is the first
of the world's megaship operators to designate an East Coast home
port. By Susan Diesenhouse.
