<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-BMW (Undated) _ The bandages are off now, and two
sedans, the first of the next-generation 3-Series, are on sale.
Enthusiasts' worries were unfounded; the operation was a success.
The '99 is more refined, and it intentionally mimics the bigger
5-Series in its features, its interior design, even its appearance.
BMW has made top-to-bottom changes, including a new body and a
couple of updated engines, but it has left the car's character _
serious but fun, solid but spritely _ essentially intact. The
3-Series has grown up, and if it has lost some adolescent spunk, it
has gained a measure of maturity. By James G. Cobb.
</P>
