those stocks sink below their sale price this year, lagging shares
of larger, better established companies. By Per H. Jebsen.
</P>
<P>
   MUTUAL-FUND-FEES-BLOOM (Boston) _ A mutual fund investor group
is joining the Securities and Exchange Commission's call for money
managers to disclose more effectively how the fees they charge take
a bite from fund performance. By Tim Quinson.
</P>
<P>
   FUND-PSYCHOLOGY-BLOOM (New York) _ Breathe easy, mutual fund
companies. Even if the U.S. suffers through a bear market for
stocks any time soon, it isn't likely that investors will abandon
their equity-oriented investments, academics and analysts say. By
Jon Friedman.
</P>
<P>
   FLOW-OF-FUNDS (Boston) _ Fidelity Investments' veteran fund
