stock market. By Tim Quinson.
</P>
<P>
   PERSONAL-WEALTH-INTERNATIONAL-FUNDS (New York) _ U.S. investors
who want to use mutual funds to diversify into foreign stocks can
find low-cost funds with superior performance and avoid paying the
high management fees that usually accompany international funds,
financial planners say. By Scott Schnipper.
</P>
<P>
   PERSONAL-FUNDS (London) _ James Seddon, who manages T. Rowe
Price's European Equity Fund, is bullish about the investment
prospects posed by the European Alliance, which begins on Jan. 1.
By Jon Friedman.
</P>
