 MANAGEMENT BOOKS WE HOPE WE NEVER SEE  &HT;     By Ilana DeBare  
 c. 1998 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
Publishers are scrambling to churn out management books based on
the lives of people like Churchill, Lincoln and Jesus. Here are a
few titles that we're NOT likely ever to see in print _ thank
goodness:
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Management by Fiddling Around: Leadership Lessons From
Emperor Nero.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``A Three-Hour Cruise: Team-Building Ideas From Gilligan's
Island.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Empowered Whaling Ship: Management Tips From Captain
Ahab.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Kill the Competition: Leadership Lessons from John Gotti.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``You Can Really Do It All: Lessons in Balancing Work &AMP; Family
From Joan of Arc.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Keeping Your Head During Times of Change: Corporate Takeover
Tips From Robespierre.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Unsinkable Corporation: Management Lessons From Edward
John Smith, Capt., RMS Titanic.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Really Casual Friday: Lessons in Corporate Dress &AMP; Etiquette
From Madonna.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Achieving Excellense: Workforce Development Tips From Homer
Simpson.''
</P>
</TEXT>
