<HEADLINE>
ACTION, NOT WORDS FOR USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Since USC is a Nike school, perhaps it's
appropriate that the Trojans have adopted a ``Just do it''
philosophy about playing UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   Several of the team's leaders have refrained from fiery
speeches, group meetings or visual reminders to underclassmen about
the Trojans' seven-game losing streak to the Bruins. All have been
tried in recent years, without success.
</P>
<P>
   ``If I have to go out and lecture someone about how important
this game is, then they don't need to be here and they don't need
to be on the field,'' senior Daylon McCutcheon said. ``A dog has it
naturally in its genes that it hates cats. That's how it is when
you're a Trojan. I never wanted to be a Bruin. I don't think I
should have to talk to anyone.''
</P>
<P>
   McCutcheon's sentiments were echoed by senior wide receiver
Billy Miller.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't talk about it, you've got to be about doing it,''
Miller said. ``We've got to go out there and prove it. We've got to
go out and play the best game of the season.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Soward update No. 101: Wide receiver R. Jay Soward did some
light running again Thursday, leading to differing opinions on his
ability to play in Saturday's game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm really encouraged by what he did,'' Hackett said. ``I
think we'll have him throwing with Carson (Palmer today). R. Jay at
80 or 85 percent is still pretty good. I'm going to anticipate
having him with two more days of treatment.''
</P>
<P>
   Others are much less optimistic, believing Soward is far from
ready to play, especially with such minimal practice time.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said he did not anticipate Soward receiving an
anti-inflammatory injection before the game. Soward has already
received three in his right ankle and tried seeing a chiropractor
to speed up his recovery.
</P>
<P>
   Soward pretended to stagger off the practice field with a
pronounced limp Thursday, to exaggerate his condition.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said he would be ``shocked'' if Soward watched the game
in street clothes.
</P>
<P>
   __ No cardinal: Hackett was surprised to learn that the Trojans
no longer wear cardinal jerseys when they play UCLA as the road
team. The last time he coached in the game in 1980, the NCAA
allowed both schools to wear their home jerseys.
</P>
<P>
   __ Receivers ready: Aside from Soward, USC should be in fairly
good shape with its receiving corps. Mike Bastianelli will play but
will have to wear a brace on his knee after suffering a sprained
medial collateral ligament against Stanford. ``I'm out here running
around, I'm playing,'' Bastianelli said.
</P>
<P>
   Quincy Woods is also available after being out much of the
season with a sore knee.
</P>
<P>
   __ All-Academic team: Tailback Chad Morton and kicker Adam
Abrams were named first-team members of the Pacific-10 Conference
All-Academic team. Brennan Ochs and Mike Van Raaphorst were named
honorable mention.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
